FILE: types.rs
MOD: stanza/types
ROLE: Stanza routing types and enrichment functions — the core contract layer for all message routing
EP: resolve_destination; resolve_agent_name; enrich_from; enrich_to_for_remote
STAB: stable
INV:
  - resolve_destination never modifies input — pure function, returns a Destination variant
  - Destination::CrossProjectChannel only produced when '#' prefix + dot present: '#ch.Proj' → channel='ch', project='Proj'
  - resolve_agent_name splits at FIRST dot only: 'Name.AITeam.Platform' → ('Name', 'AITeam.Platform')
  - enrich_from and enrich_to_for_remote scope ALL replacements to the opening tag only (split at first '>')
  - Body content (everything after first '>') is NEVER modified by any function in this file
  - enrich_from is idempotent: already-qualified from= passes through unchanged
  - enrich_to_for_remote is idempotent: already-qualified to= passes through unchanged
  - ResolvedMention is produced by resolve_mentions (dispatch layer) — delivery layer must not re-resolve
LOOK: enrich_from tests; enrich_to_for_remote tests; resolve_destination channel/cross-project split logic
CHK: Run cargo test stanza after any change; verify body-content invariant tests still pass
CNTR: stanza/types::enrich_from used_by broker/delivery::deliver
CNTR: stanza/types::resolve_destination used_by broker/state::dispatch_stanza
CNTR: stanza/types::ResolvedMention compatible_with broker/delivery::deliver_to_mentions
